## Summary
This documentation explains how Amplitude identifies users through device IDs, Amplitude IDs, and user IDs, emphasizing that user IDs are optional but recommended for cross-device tracking and event reconciliation, with important implementation guidelines including that user IDs cannot be changed once set and should not be assigned to anonymous users.

